review_blob: Better than champagne for breakfast! Mix with Guinness for a Belgian black velvet. Fruity, bubbly, subversively strong.
A sweet gold bock.  One of my favorites (when on sale, of course).
What happens when you drink Bass ale while eating pumpkin pie? This beer.
beer_name: Buffalo Bills Americas Original Pumpkin Ale

review_blob: Great camping beer, great value.
Beats drinking plain water.
It was free with dinner -- beats drinking wine.
Very good body, rich malt taste. A fine ESB on tap locally.
Good pale ale, although other brews offered (which I forget already) were more adventuresome. Easy brewpub to find even if youre not local.

beer_brewer_name: Portland Brewing Company (Pyramid - North American Breweries)
review_blob: Tinny aftertaste, initial burst of carbonation tapers to leave a creamy, if temporary head. I prefer GBs Marzen (when on sale) to this.
Pour it in a glass and fool your friends. Taste better than most lights and way cheaper!
The defacto dry stout. Had it in London where it was pulled properly. Very enjoyable.
Had on tap in London. Head stayed on the glass the whole drink. Nice aroma, great with fish n chips.
Had it on draft in Lucern. Good average lager. Still better than any Budmilloors has to offer.
Dark color, light body, generic amber. Allows for drinking several with no adverse affects.
Best on draft (in Paris). Actually, about the only beer available on draft in Paris.  A good beer when you dont drink wine.
Light, clean, sorta sweet. About the only beer on tap in Rome. Great after walking about Rome all day.
Classic ale with a mild bite. Not bad in a (fresh) bottle.
Thin body with a thick taste.  Best light beer Ive tried. Best of all it was free.
Lemony, citrus-y, very fizzy. Great when on sale.
Smooth and strong.
